comment: Note: this is not a well-developed organic horizon, it is pretty weak, yet can be differentiated from the lower mineral horizon
Yellow means that data is being confirmed on 9/19/15
The AT has some striving seedlings from the seed experiment.
Interestingly, the T and the F do not have seedlings that are thriving.
Uncertain why seedings that regenerated in 2015 were gone. Buried by needles?
Seeds may have been eaten by the bird, siskins
The organic horizon is well developed
The herbs rot in the late fall making a slimy layer that covers the organic layer that seems to have silty particles.
